       true,
       "itertools.combinations.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('object') == True — combinations is a C extension type that inherits directly from object; __bases__ is a tuple containing exactly one entry (object); __bases__[0].__name__ is 'object'; str.__eq__('object') returns True; no prior itertools spec checks combinations.__bases__[0].__name__ via itertoolsmrod87; new to extra87"]
    - [permutations_base_name_eq_object,
