       "itertools.permutations.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('object') == True — permutations is a C extension type that inherits directly from object; __bases__ is a tuple containing exactly one entry (object); __bases__[0].__name__ is 'object'; str.__eq__('object') returns True; no prior itertools spec checks permutations.__bases__[0].__name__ via itertoolsmrod87; new to extra87"]

